description.narrative: By 2021, WCAR countries have increased capacity to develop and implement sectoral policies, plans and programs to protect children and adolescents, particularly girls from HIV transmission and keep them AIDS-Free (Start-Free Stay-Free AIDS-free) with a particular focus on 10 countries (6 high HIV burden and 4 high prevalence)., which contributes to Hiv Prevention, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every woman, newborn, child and adolescent has an equal chance to survive and thrive

description.narrative: In 2021, WCARO supported countries toward their effort to reach 2025 targets, with tailored technical assistance for the adoption and implementation of proven high-impact strategies and interventions to increase access to quality HIV services and reduce new infections. ART coverage among children 0-14 years has increased to 36% in 2020 vs. 29% in 2018; PMTCT is stagnating at 56% while EID decreased to 27% vs. 34% in 2019. These regional trends hide important progress made at country-level, with 4 countries having ART coverage 45-61%, 8 countries with EID coverage between 30-61%, and 5 countries with PMTCT coverage higher than 80%.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/02/2022
